article.headline: Montana 57, Montana St.-Northern 43
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Brian Qvale scored 23 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Montana to a 57-43 victory over NAIA Montana State-Northern on Wednesday night. Qvale, who missed the last two games to be with his ill father in North Dakota, shot 9 for 11 from the field in his return and anchored the Grizzlies down low. Montana (7-4) finished with a 38-25 rebounding edge. Justin Dennis scored 13 points to lead Montana State-Northern. The Grizzlies were 23 of 43 from the field and limited Montana State-Northern to 32-percent shooting. Jack McGillis was the only other Montana player to score in double figures, finishing with 10. The Grizzlies held a 31-18 advantage at the break. Their lead swelled to as many as 17 early in the second, before the Lights closed to within 39-31 with 11:37 remaining. Montana responded with a 14-4 run to put the game out of reach.
